# Welcome {-}
The fact that you are here suggest you have an interest to do population modeling in R ! Maybe you found this through our [nlmixr website](http://nlmixr.org/wp/). Maybe via [Twitter](https://twitter.com/nlmixr), [LinkedIn](https://www.linkedin.com/start/join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fgroups%2F8621368&trk=login_reg_redirect), [GitHub](https://github.com/nlmixrdevelopment/nlmixr). Either way: **welcome and join us in our journey to do population modeling in R !**

This book is intended to get you started with `nlmixr: an R package for population PKPD modeling`. You'll get information on the package itself, its installation, interesting use cases and more.

```{r logo-fig, fig.cap='', out.width='80%', fig.asp=.75, fig.align='center', echo=FALSE}
knitr::include_graphics("logo.png")
```

